TITLE: Seattle man rescued after house slides off foundation following heavy rain
SUMMARY: Seattle firefighters rescued a man trapped in the basement of his house after it "slid 15-20 feet off its foundation" during a landslide, authorities said Friday.

TITLE: A 6-year-old was found dead in Indiana after going missing for 4 days
SUMMARY: A 6-year-old boy who was last seen on January 4 was found dead near an abandoned house in Gary, Indiana early Saturday morning.

TITLE: New Orleans City Council votes unanimously to rename Robert E. Lee Blvd for legendary musician Allen Toussaint
SUMMARY: The New Orleans City Council voted unanimously Thursday to change the name of Robert E. Lee Boulevard to Allen Toussaint Boulevard, councilmember Jared C. Brossett confirmed to CNN Saturday.

TITLE: The death of a man who caught on fire after being tased by police is under investigation
SUMMARY: The New York attorney general's office is investigating an incident in which a man died weeks after catching fire when police tased him while he was covered in hand sanitizer, new videos released on Friday by the attorney general's office show.

TITLE: South Dakota places further restrictions on medication abortions
SUMMARY: Women in South Dakota who are seeking a medication abortion will face additional restrictions later this month after state lawmakers approved a new rule from the state's health department.

TITLE: Biden eulogizes Reid as 'one of the greatest Senate Majority Leaders in history'
SUMMARY: Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid was remembered by a host of top Democratic politicians at his memorial service in Las Vegas on Saturday, with former President Barack Obama recalling him as a fighter "who did not give up" and President Joe Biden hailing the Nevada Democrat as someone who "would always have your back."

TITLE: Sen. John Thune will run for re-election
SUMMARY: South Dakota Sen. John Thune, the No. 2 Republican in the Senate, announced Saturday he is running for re-election in 2022.

TITLE: Analysis: Ted Cruz told the truth about the 1/6 attack. Then he started backtracking.
SUMMARY: On Wednesday, Sen. Ted Cruz told the truth about what happened at the US Capitol on January 6, 2021, calling it "a violent terrorist attack on the Capitol, where we saw the men and women of law enforcement demonstrate incredible courage."

TITLE: Why Nike, Adidas and Ralph Lauren stuff is getting tougher to find
SUMMARY: Looking to buy Nike sneakers, Adidas sweats, Crocs clogs, Polo shirts or Canada Goose parkas?

TITLE: Need a raise? Now's the time to demand one
SUMMARY: If you haven't secured a raise in a while, now's the time to make your move.

TITLE: Citigroup to fire unvaccinated employees this month
SUMMARY: Citigroup staff in the United States who have not been vaccinated against Covid-19 by Jan. 14 will be placed on unpaid leave and fired at the end of the month unless they are granted an exemption, a source familiar with the matter said on Friday.

TITLE: In a turbulent year for theaters, Disney still won the box office
SUMMARY: In a turbulent year when the pandemic continued to upend the business of movie-going and streaming blockbusters at home became commonplace, one thing returned to normal: Disney topped the box office.
